## Grammar

- Simple present tense with common verbs (eat, love, play, can, become)
- Personal pronouns (אני, אתה, את, הוא, היא, אנחנו)
- יש/אין expressing existence and possession
- Introduction of gender distinction (מְשַׂחֵק/מְשַׂחֶקֶת, יָכוֹל/יְכוֹלָה)
- Copula omission or replacement with יש in present tense
- Using adjectives after nouns (שֵׂעָר בָּהִיר, מִּשְׁפָּחָה גְּדוֹלָה)
- Basic construct phrases (בֵּין הַיְלָדִים)
- Definite article usage (הַ) before nouns and adjectives
